              {
                "severity": "blocking",
                "file": "internal/builders/go.go",
                "lines": "248-270",
                "category": "pragmatic/dead-abstraction",
                "diagnosis": "discoverBinariesFromProxy duplicates the request+size-limit+read pattern from downloadArtifact (artifact.go:39-102) verbatim -- User-Agent, LimitReader with +1 truncation detection, size check, status check. The context note says downloadArtifact was skipped because it enforces HTTPS-only and would break HTTP test mocks, but that means the shared helper has an undocumented gap that silently forces duplication. Either (a) add an allowHTTP option to downloadArtifactOptions for test use, or (b) add a prominent comment in discoverBinariesFromProxy explaining the deliberate non-use of downloadArtifact and why, so the next developer doesn't merge the two and break tests. Without that comment the duplication is a maintenance trap: two places to update User-Agent, timeout logic, or size constants."
